<TITLE> Four drown as boat sinks in Narsingdi storm </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narsingdi, May 26 (bdnews24.com)Four drowned in the river Meghna when an overloaded ferry boat capsized in the midst of the storm near Duttapara ferry point on Monday. Another one is in critical condition. The boat, heading towards Char Budiamara with around 50 people on board, edged into a maelstrom when it reached the middle of the river at around 7:30pm, said officer-in-charge of Narsingdi Police Station Jahangir Bhuiyan. Many of the passengers swam to the bank of the river soon after the boat went down. The dead are Nurul Islam Muhuri, 50, and Ramjan Mia, 25, from Kalai Govindapur under Sadar Upazila; Jalu Mia, 26, from Dorinobipur and Joj Mia, 35, from Jamaliakandi. Nazrul Islam, 40, from Kalai Govindapur, was rescued and sent to the Dhaka Medical College Hospital in critical state. bdn
